Package au.edu.anu.twcore.data.runtime

Class DataLabel

java.lang.Object
au.edu.anu.twcore.data.runtime.DataLabel
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Comparable<DataLabel>
Direct Known Subclasses:
DataIdentifier, IndexedDataLabel
public class DataLabel extends Object implements Comparable<DataLabel>, Cloneable
The toString() method of this class is a hotspot problem in SpatialWidget and maybe elsewhere. The thing is that this class has a 'construction' phase and what is effectively a read-only phase. So a simple solution would be a lazyToString method that calls toString only if the a string prop is null. However, for widgets this shouldn't effect sim speed as they are in a different thread. Will try and see
Author:
Ian Davies
